The paper presents a new algorithm for evolving the structure of convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the evolved networks on image classification tasks, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of volunteer computing also suggests a potential fit for distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for further improvement using advanced techniques, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents results on test data accuracy, which could also fit under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
